.TH "flush_work" 9 "flush_work" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
flush_work \- wait for a work to finish executing the last queueing instance
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" flush_work
.BI "(struct work_struct *work "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "work" 12
the work to flush
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Wait until \fIwork\fP has finished execution.  \fIwork\fP is guaranteed to be idle
on return if it hasn't been requeued since flush started.
.SH "RETURN"
true if \fBflush_work\fP waited for the work to finish execution,
false if it was already idle.
